      • multiSourceMultiSink

        public static RheemPlan multiSourceMultiSink(java.util.List<java.lang.String> inputList1,
                                             java.util.List<java.lang.String> inputList2,
                                             java.util.List<java.lang.String> collector1,
                                             java.util.List<java.lang.String> collector2)
        Creates a RheemPlan with two CollectionSources and two LocalCallbackSinks. Both sources go into a UnionAllOperator and for the first LocalCallbackSink, the data quanta are routed via a MapOperator that applies String.toUpperCase().

      • multiSourceHoleMultiSink

        public static RheemPlan multiSourceHoleMultiSink(java.util.List<java.lang.String> inputList1,
                                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> inputList2,
                                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> collector1,
                                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> collector2)
        Creates a RheemPlan with two CollectionSources and two LocalCallbackSinks. Both sources go into a UnionAllOperator. Then, the data flow diverges again and to the branches one MapOperator is applied with String.toUpperCase() and String.toLowerCase(). Finally, the both branches are united via another UnionAllOperator, which is in turn consumed by the two LocalCallbackSinks.
